{meta: title It's A Long Way From Heaven}
{meta: artist Norma Jean}
{meta: composer Sharon Higgins and Jimmie Helms}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Word got back to me you said it’s heaven to be [D7]free
[G]So I looked in on your world but no heaven could I see
[C]Smoke is standing in your eyes that made your vision dim
[G]It’s a long way from [D7]heaven to the world you’re living [G]in
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]Heaven don’t have swinging doors and bottles on the [G]table
[C]The great big purple grapes of wrath printed on the [D7]label
[G]Both are angels wearing dresses tighter than their [C]skin
[G]It’s a long way from [D7]heaven to the world you’re living [G]in
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[D7]Maybe you would rather be without my love and fancy free
